# =============================================================================
# Template-repo hygiene: what must NOT travel when this vault is cloned as a
# new knowledge base. The committed baseline (schema, specs, scripts,
# .claude/settings.json with the portable guard hook) travels; everything
# below is machine-/vault-specific and re-accretes or is re-created per clone.
# =============================================================================

# --- Personal Claude Code permission grants (project-scoped; re-accretes per clone) ---
# "Don't ask again" writes here. Kept out of the repo so each clone starts clean
# and builds its own local allow-list. The shared baseline lives in .claude/settings.json.
.claude/settings.local.json

# --- SECRETS: Obsidian Local REST API key lives in the plugin's data.json ---
# Never ship one vault's API key to another (each vault gets its own — see
# checklist.new-wiki-project §3c). This is the most important line here.
.obsidian/plugins/*/data.json

# --- Obsidian per-user UI state (churns constantly, machine-specific) ---
.obsidian/workspace.json
.obsidian/workspace-mobile.json

# --- Obsidian trash & OS cruft ---
.trash/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# --- Optional: uncomment to reinstall plugins per-vault (checklist §3a) instead ---
# of shipping their code in the template. Left tracked by default so a fresh
# clone is "para-drop and go" with the MCP plugin already present.
# .obsidian/plugins/
